Others: Paolo Banchero returned to the court after missing 34 games due to a torn right oblique.
Banchero scored 34 points, seven rebounds, three assists, two steals, and a block in his return game.
Banchero shot efficiently, going 11-for-22 from the field, 5-for-8 from three, and 7-for-10 from the free throw line.
Before his injury, Banchero was averaging 29 points, 8.8 rebounds, and 5.6 assists per game.
Banchero recorded a career-high 50 points in a win over the Indiana Pacers on October 28.
Head coach Jamahl Mosley praised Banchero's performance, emphasizing his poise and determination.
